# Project Rules: Platform Documentation

## Project Context

This is a **product documentation project** for a workflow-driven IT Service Management and IT Asset Management platform. The documentation is conceptual and architectural, not operational.

**Platform:** Alloy Navigator (Alloy Software)

### Documentation Sources

When verifying platform capabilities or technical facts, consult:

| Source | URL / Location |
|--------|----------------|
| **Official Online Docs** | https://docs.alloysoftware.com |
| **Local Documentation** | `OnlineDocs` folder (bundled with product installation) |

---

## Platform Technical Facts

These are verified technical constraints of the Alloy Navigator platform:

### Work Order / Ticket Hierarchy

- **Work Order SUPPORTS parent-child hierarchy (recursion)**
- Work Order can have subordinate (child) Work Orders
- Hierarchy supports multiple levels: children, grandchildren, etc.
- Views available: All Descendants, Children Only, Hierarchy Tree
- Parent Ticket field identifies the parent Work Order
- Cumulative Time Spent sums time across parent and all subordinates
- Source: https://docs.alloysoftware.com/alloynavigator/help/webportal/content/service-support-and-projects/work-orders-tab.htm

### Incident Hierarchy (Enterprise)

- **Incident does NOT support parent-child hierarchy** in current Enterprise version
- Incident has Related Problem, Related Change Request fields, but NO Parent Incident field
- Incident can have subordinate **Work Orders** (decomposition)
- Cumulative Time Spent sums time across Incident and its Work Orders
- Source: https://docs.alloysoftware.com/alloynavigator/help/webportal/content/service-support-and-projects/general-tab-incident.htm

### Express Edition: Two Ticket Types

In Express, there are effectively **two types of Tickets** based on their role in hierarchy:

| Template | Type | Can be Parent? | Can be Child? | Notes |
|----------|------|----------------|---------------|-------|
| **Quick Request [#840]** | Primary ticket | ✓ Yes | ✓ Yes | Standalone or parent, available in Desktop/Web/Mobile |
| **Quick Task (Child) [#841]** | Child ticket | ✓ Yes | ✓ Yes (designed for this) | Created via Child Tickets tab, marked with "This template creates child tickets" |

**Key point:** Quick Task is **specifically designed** to be a subordinate ticket. Its template has the "This template creates child tickets" checkbox and is only available through the Child Tickets tab of a parent ticket.

- Source: https://docs.alloysoftware.com/alloynavigatorexpress/docs/adminguide/adminguide/workflow-management/configuring-workflow-templates/customizing-create-ticket-forms.htm

